 I am willing to give away the secret for free during this special occasion 

00:01:03.300 --> 00:01:06.440
 It has to do with the interaction between, 

00:01:06.640 --> 00:01:12.280
 the intrinsic, or inner dimension, of the sheet of paper that is 2 dimensions. 

00:01:12.280 --> 00:01:17.040
 And the fact that the skin evolves and flourishes in the surrounding three-dimensional space. 

00:01:17.160 --> 00:01:19.780
 There is an elbow room, there is some ambient space. 

00:01:19.780 --> 00:01:22.160
 So dimension 2 and dimension 3. 

00:01:22.160 --> 00:01:23.260
 In the following sense. 

00:01:23.260 --> 00:01:27.100
 First, I can fold the paper in a naive way as follows, 

00:01:27.100 --> 00:01:31.960
 in which case the largest opening I can try to let the disk through is this space. 

00:01:32.100 --> 00:01:34.460
 That was previously, as you can see, 

00:01:34.460 --> 00:01:36.620
 the diagonal of the square hole 

00:01:36.620 --> 00:01:39.620
 And that was too small to let the disk through. 

00:01:39.620 --> 00:01:41.420
 But that's not the only thing we do. 

00:01:41.420 --> 00:01:45.680
 Now I take this sheet of paper and start turning it 

00:01:45.780 --> 00:01:50.660
 until those two sides are aligned in a straight line 

00:01:50.660 --> 00:01:53.620
 And while I do this, while turning the ends 

00:01:53.620 --> 00:01:58.040
 you can see that the part of the paper is starting to rise above the floor. 

00:01:58.120 --> 00:02:00.240
 That is escape to the 3rd dimension, 

00:02:00.240 --> 00:02:02.740
 take advantage of the fact that there is extra space there. 

00:02:02.740 --> 00:02:06.035
 And when those two sides fully align 

00:02:06.040 --> 00:02:07.980
 Then I can crush and fold. 

